            <div type="translation" resp="part:reda part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1"> 		
                    Prosperity! Fortune!
                </p>
                
                <p n="1-3">
                 This is the 34th year of the king Kulottuṅga Cōḻa <supplied reason="subaudible">III</supplied>.
                </p>
                
                <p n="4-17">
                    I, Amattai, also known as Araiyaṉ Irumuṭicōḻa Muvaraiyaṉ from Karuppūr, after engraving it on stone for the Lord Nalla Nāyaṉār of Nallūr as <foreign>tēvatāṉam</foreign> for this Lord, after excluding
                <list>
                    <item>360 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s of land from Nallūr,</item>
                    <item>5 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s of land for the sacred garden on the northern bank of the river, and</item>
                    <item>5 <foreign>vēli</foreign>s of paddy fields from Kāccuvakuṭi,</item>
                </list>
                </p>
                <p>
                     I have given the 5 <foreign>mā</foreign>s of land, the taxes for watching the lands <supplied reason="subaudible"><foreign>pāṭikāval</foreign></supplied>, all types of <seg cert="low">state</seg> taxes <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āyam</foreign></supplied>,  and minor cesses <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kīḻ iṟai pāṭṭam</foreign></supplied>, <supplied reason="omitted">which include</supplied> the tax on loom <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>taṟi iṟai</foreign></supplied>.
                </p>
                <p n="17-19">
                    Whoever destroys <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>aḻittu kōḷvāṉ</foreign></supplied> this inscription will become himself the husband <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>maṇavāḷaṉ</foreign></supplied> to his own mother <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ammaikku tāṉē</foreign></supplied>.
                </p>
                <p n="19-20">
                    This is under the protection of the <foreign>maheśvara</foreign>s.
                </p>
            </div>
            
